  "subject": "Don't remove PDPs when heart beat missed",
  "commit_message": "Don't remove PDPs when heart beat missed\n\nModified PAP so that, if a heart beat is missed from a PDP, instead of\nremoving the PDP from the DB, it simply sends a state-change message\nto the PDP.  Only after the PDP fails to respond to the state-change\ndoes PAP remove the PDP from the DB.\nModified code to count missed heart beats and only generate a message\nwhen they've been missed several times.\nAlso noticed that some of the junits seems to be failing intermittently,\nso modified the two relevant tests to allocate separate ports on which\nto run the PAP.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-2326\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\nChange-Id: Idd5950ffd0afb1f73df5c4dc2552441097f7528f\n",
